  "body": "<!-- **Are you in the right place?**\r\n1. For issues or feature requests, please create an issue in this repository.\r\n2. For general technical and non-technical questions, we are happy to help you on our [Rook.io Slack](https://slack.rook.io/).\r\n3. Did you already search the existing open issues for anything similar? -->\r\n\r\n**Is this a bug report or feature request?**\r\n* Feature Request\r\n\r\n**What should the feature do:**\r\nPost creation of ceph cluster, Rook should deploy the ceph alerting rules. The steps required for the same would be as below\r\n* Enable monitoring for namespace in which Ceph is deployed (e.g. openshift-storage)\r\n  oc label namespace openshift-storage openshift.io/cluster-monitoring=true\r\n  oc policy add-role-to-user view system:serviceaccount:openshift-monitoring:prometheus-k8s -n openshift-storage\r\n* Create service monitor with ceph's namespace\r\n```\r\napiVersion: monitoring.coreos.com/v1\r\nkind: ServiceMonitor\r\nmetadata:\r\n  labels:\r\n    team: rook\r\n  name: rook-ceph-mgr\r\n  namespace: openshift-storage\r\nspec:\r\n  endpoints:\r\n  - interval: 5s\r\n    path: /metrics\r\n    port: http-metrics\r\n  namespaceSelector:\r\n    matchNames:\r\n    - openshift-storage\r\n  selector:\r\n    matchLabels:\r\n      app: rook-ceph-mgr\r\n      rook_cluster: openshift-storage\r\n```\r\n* Deploy the ceph alerting rule file\r\n\r\n\r\n**What is use case behind this feature:**\r\nAlerting for ceph cluster\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n<!-- Specific environment information that helps with the feature request -->\r\n",
